## 12. Common Mistakes & Key Takeaways

| Mistake | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Vague headlines | Be specific — numbers, names, outcomes |
| Clickbait that misleads | Curiosity without misrepresentation |
| One headline per article | Generate 5-10 variants and test |
| Ignoring platform | Adapt for LinkedIn vs Twitter vs email |

| # | Takeaway |
|---|----------|
| 1 | **Multi-style generation** produces diverse options |
| 2 | **Platform-specific headlines** outperform one-size-fits-all |
| 3 | **Emotional framing** changes how same facts are perceived |
| 4 | **Data-driven headlines** score highest on click-appeal |
| 5 | **Rule-based captures facts** but LLMs add the angle |

